                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the east wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Śivāṅkurēśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Vikramapāṇḍya. Year 4: 1253 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>The details of date given, viz., <hi rend="bold">Kumbha, śu. 3, Sunday, Uttiram</hi> will correspond to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1253, February 2, Sunday</hi>, ·71, ·76, if the <hi rend="italic">nakshatra</hi> Uttiram is taken as a mistake for Uttirāḍam.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This inscription registers the gift of 20 <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> of land by Tāmandai Vēḷān Tiruvaṇṇāmalai Uḍaiyāṉ Teṉṉavarāyaṉ of Peruṅganūr in Pañchavaṉmādēvipuram, in Kuvaḷaiya-nāḍu in Rājarāja-vaḷanāḍu to the <hi rend="italic">kaṇkāṇikaraṇattār</hi> of the temple of Tiruttiṉainagaruḍaiyār as <hi rend="italic">tirunāmattukkāṇi</hi> (<hi rend="italic">See</hi> No. <ref target="DHARMA_INSSIIv17p0i0122">122</ref> above). </p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
